        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">1) Feign Death doesn't give any indication to the caster that it's worked. In heavy combat it can be hard to tell if it when off or not. The caster is told if the spell didn't work "Soandso has fallen to the ground." and if it does work *others* see "Soandso dies.". If would be nice if the caster got the "dies" message. A spell icon would be even better, but I can see where that might be a problem if you already had 15 effects on you. <BR>2) Tap type spells wear off twice. Spells like Siphon Strength and Shroud of Hate have their own message when they wear of. But you also get the stock yellow "Your xyzzy spell has worn off.". For example: </P><P>Your Shroud of Hate spell has worn off. <BR>The hatred departs. </P><P>It might make sense to get the yellow message if the MOB you cast the spell on was still alive, but you get it when they are long dead as well. However if you zone before the spell wears off you get only the spell's message and not the yellow one </P><P>3) Dead Man Floating doesn't stack with Deadeye (self only see invs/infravision). Both have see invs, which might explain it, but the See Invisible spell does stack with Deadeye and I'm pretty sure that Infravision stacks with DMF. It all seems pretty odd. It is true that DMF should not overwrite Deadeye as infravision would be lost. </P><P>1) Having played a high level Shadow Knight, I agree there are times when I will not notice my spell going off. However when I get into situations where I think I'm going to need to FD/DP I just pop into 3rd person mode so I can see my character. </P><P>2) I'm sure you understand why you get two messages. The effect is on you, and the NPC. When it wears off it wears off from both of you which is why the double message. That being said I doubt we will get this changed any time soon. </P><P>3)These spells should stack with each other. I'll modify Deadeye and throw it up on test and see if any other stacking issues arise from the change. </P><P>- Lawrence Poe </P><P><BR>sigh</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
