        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">"I got bids that they will probably give our class a ton of upgrades this patch and actually decrease the magres on the god mobs and also let our life taps unresist now:D<BR>Any takers?"</P><P>If your going to be sarcastic, you may as well go all the way, like this:</P><P>'We are going to change Necro pets back to the way they were upon the initial release of EQ.  Additionally, the 50+ pets are going to be greatly enhanced to make them superior to all lower level pets, as they should be.  All lifetaps are going back to their unresistable state, just like they used to be.  Feign Death will work like it used to, at any level.  DoTs will be resisted normally, even on gods.  Screaming Terror will make mobs run away, and clear the hate list, just like it was intended to when we announced it would be replacing Charm.  And speaking of Charm, we are going to give Necros that (and of course, Beguile) back too.  Also, we are going to get rid of the stupid night time only restriction on any Necro spells that have it.  Not sure why that was put in anyway.'</P><P>Heh, I just read through what I had just written, and the sad thing is if they did just that, and nothing more, all they would be doing is putting Necros back to the way we used to be, and we would actually be quite nicely balanced!  So I guess it all boils down to if Verant hadn't had a knee-jerk reaction to nerfing the Necro class and just left it alone, we'd pretty much be balanced right now.  Just goes to show you sometimes it's better to let problems solve themselves rather than constantly messing with something until it's worse than when you started.</P><P><IMG src="http://members.spree.com/funngames/qazjax/manapump.jpg"></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
