        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">VI would like to officially state the reasoning for the following changes.</P><P>The Necromancer has the highest difficulty rating of any caster class.</P><P>Our view of difficulty includes:<BR>KOS on average, disliked at the least<BR>Lack of quests in home town<BR>Lack of doable quests in game<BR>Extreme faction work<BR>Lack of spells on vendors that like you - oh you want shielding, go see the wizard vendor, LOL or the cleric<BR>Lack of vendor for component for spells - bone chips<BR>Few vendors for needed component - oh want a coffin eh?  Be back in an hour<BR>Few volunteers to make component - oh sure, sacrifice away<BR>Must research for spells - words off mobs you can't kill yet</P><P>In return however we have made the following changes<BR>- Necro pets are undead.  Only undead only spells will affect them.  Normal fear, charm, etc will not.<BR>- Necro pets once again use the speed of weapons.  This is balanced because the necro cannot summon a weapon and will have to lug around a bag of daggers<BR>- New AI with new spell for necro pets.  The 44+ pets will now turn on any add not instructed to be killed and screaming terror it<BR>- Lifetap is unresistable.  This is balanced because it costs so much to cast and does so little damage, but is essential to the functionality of the necro.  With the new server side filtering, VI accepts the Xerg gang rape tactic.<BR>- We apologize for the HP of the 50+ pets.  The 53 & 56 pets have had their HPs tripled and the 59 has had it's doubled<BR>- The 59 component cost remains.  However, it now summons a level 55 warrior pet every time.  Oh, and it procs Avatar.<BR>- We really apologize about the DOT given to the magicians at 55.  It's now Necro also.<BR>- Screaming terror will now mez 5 seconds longer for every level over 50.<BR>- Infusion will CH your mana pool.<BR>- Trucidation is irresistable and does 5000 damage for 50 mana.  The wizards can be quiet since we left in the 15 minute recast and component.  If someone has to die to use it, it should damn well hurt.  Not to mention we like to think of it as the UnHoly Hand Grenade.</P><P></P><P>Sigh.  I can dream can't I?</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

